The paper deals with the theoretical analysis and computation of equilibrium in security games, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the use of optimization techniques and algorithms to solve security games, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and combinatorial optimization (cs.DS). The paper also touches upon the application of security games in various domains, including computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.SI).
